    "as the regularization function, which favors smoother s(β).",
    "It can be given a small or large weight, relative to χ 2, for gentle or aggressive smoothing, as desired.",
    "Further developments of the idea appear in several later works (Suyu et al. 2006; Vegetti and Koopmans 2009; Vernardos et al. 202).",
    "An advantage of a quadratic regularization function like (75) is that the minimization procedure requires solving only linear equations.",
    "But it is not a requirement, and source reconstruction using more complicated regularization functions is also possible, notably in the early work by Kochanek et al. (1989) and later in Brewer and Lewis (2006)."
